t\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing code coverage issues**\\n\\nI’ve noticed many parts are untracked and the existing tree is messy. The report suggests previous coverage issues might stem from not including our generated direct access class in the workflow. It seems the generated helper isn’t in the source, and dynamic agents track library classes only. I’m wondering if tests didn't run due to the filename containing \\\"closure6.\\\" Also, the public API may not have executed what it needed due to the intricacies of closure6's structure. Let’s explore this further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring closure test issues**\\n\\nI noticed that for closure5, prior tests used a direct access helper. The public API by itself won’t cover that call, and I need direct access for closure6. It’s possible that the generated helper replacement didn’t work or the class isn't available. The report indicates previous attempts with no new coverage. I wonder if the issue lies in test imports or if the generated helper was invalid. It might be that the coverage instrumentation excludes synthetic calls from generated helpers. I’ll need to dive deeper!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining bytecode and access issues**\\n\\nI’m exploring alternatives, like using a package-access Java class from `io.restassured.internal` instead of the generated helper. However, that won't compile due to synthetic package-private visibility. I wonder if the generated helper wasn't packaged into the native image. It seems it is, but perhaps the tests still couldn’t load it. If there was a compile failure, there wouldn’t be a report, yet it indicates no coverage—possibly from old tests. I need to investigate further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring javap usage**\\n\\nI need to use the `javap -c` command and make sure to include the classpath with the necessary library in order to see the details correctly. It's really important to get that right so I can access the proper information about my Java classes. I'll double-check the classpath and ensure all required libraries are properly set up for this command to work as expected. Alright, let's dive into this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Qg0nEVptnb9rTYPcL5pL1YWX|fc_0348f2e07a610749016a014a458cfc81a192f30703059dd881", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath /tmp/closure6/patch:tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build/jacoco/effective/rest_assured_5_5_0_jar -c -p io.restassured.internal.ResponseSpecificationImplHamcrestAssertionClosureValidateHeadersAndCookiesClosure6DirectAccess | sed -n '1,80p'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4938, "output": 1007, "cacheRead": 94208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 100153, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778469426690, "responseId": "resp_0348f2e07a610749016a014a33832881a1880b001076e00c92"}}
